Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.name: id
Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.abstract: The unique id of the error. This is primarily used for caching

Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.name: key
Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.abstract: The key for the error. This is used by ErrorSubscriber and ErrorPublisher to route errors

Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.name: reason
Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.abstract: Describe the reason the error occured, optional

Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.name: code
Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.abstract: An error code, if applicable. Default is 0

Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.name: context
Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.abstract: Add any additional context to the error that you’d like to add

Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.name: original
Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.abstract: The original error (usually set through a Transform)

Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.name: publish(to:)
Structs/PublishableError.html#/s:14Error.abstract: Publishes this error to a specified publisher

Structs/ErrorKey.html.name: ErrorKey
Structs/ErrorKey.html.abstract: PubishableErrors have an ErrorKey, which is used to route errors in Error Publisher

Protocols/ErrorSubscriber.html#/s:14Erro.name: receiveError(_:)
Protocols/ErrorSubscriber.html#/s:14Erro.abstract: Receive a publishable error. This gets called when an error with the proper key(s)

Protocols/ObjectType.html.name: ObjectType
Protocols/ObjectType.html.abstract: A protocol to make your structs and classes identifiable by id or createdAt date

Classes/ErrorLogger.html#/s:14ErrorPubli.name: errors
Classes/ErrorLogger.html#/s:14ErrorPubli.abstract: A log of all of the errors this ErrorLogger has received

Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.name: subscribe(_:forKeys:)
Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.abstract: Register a subscriber to this publisher for various keys

Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.name: subscribe(_:forKey:)
Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.abstract: Register a subscriber to this publisher for one key

Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.name: subscribe(_:)
Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.abstract: Register a subscriber to this publisher for all keys

Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.name: unsubscribe(_:forKeys:)
Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.abstract: Remove a specific subscriber from receiving errors on a set of keys, or all keys

Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.name: unsubscribe(_:forKey:)
Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.abstract: Remove a specific subscriber from receiving errors on a specific error key

Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.name: unsubscribe(_:)
Classes/ErrorPublisher.html#/s:14ErrorPu.abstract: Remove a specific subscriber from all keys

Classes/Object.html.name: Object
Classes/Object.html.abstract: An Object class that has an id and a createdAt value, for easy indexing

Classes/ErrorPublisher.html.name: ErrorPublisher
Classes/ErrorPublisher.html.abstract: ErrorPublisher allows you to subscribe to and publish errors

Classes/ErrorLogger.html.name: ErrorLogger
Classes/ErrorLogger.html.abstract: A simple Error Logger that also remembers every error it receives
